COVID-19 Death, Political Standing Map, and GDP

# select the needed columns
# combine two Political Standing colums and define
full_ForMap1 <- full %>%
  dplyr::select(state,Cases.1M.pop,Deaths.1M.pop,Clinton,Trump,GDP_perCapita) %>%
  mutate(Poli_standing = case_when(
    Clinton > Trump ~ "Clinton",
    Clinton < Trump ~ "Trump"))

# four states are very close
# Trump got Michigan, Pennsylvania, Wisconsin; Clinton got New Hampshire
full_ForMap1$Poli_standing <- replace_na(full_ForMap1$Poli_standing,"Trump")
full_ForMap1$Poli_standing[30] <- "Clinton"

# log transformation
full_ForMap1$Deaths.1M.pop <- log(full_ForMap1$Deaths.1M.pop)
full_ForMap1$Cases.1M.pop <- log(full_ForMap1$Cases.1M.pop)
full_ForMap1$GDP_perCapita <- log(full_ForMap1$GDP_perCapita)

Clinton_Map <- full_ForMap1 %>%
  dplyr::select(state,Cases.1M.pop,Deaths.1M.pop,Poli_standing,GDP_perCapita) %>%
  filter(Poli_standing=="Clinton")

Trump_Map <- full_ForMap1 %>%
  dplyr::select(state,Cases.1M.pop,Deaths.1M.pop,Poli_standing,GDP_perCapita) %>%
  filter(Poli_standing=="Trump")

reg1 <- lm(Deaths.1M.pop ~ GDP_perCapita, data = Clinton_Map)
# summary(reg1)
reg2 <- lm(Deaths.1M.pop ~ GDP_perCapita, data = Trump_Map)
# summary(reg2)
reg3 <- lm(Cases.1M.pop ~ GDP_perCapita, data = Clinton_Map)
# summary(reg3)
reg4 <- lm(Cases.1M.pop ~ GDP_perCapita, data = Trump_Map)
# summary(reg4)

ggplot() +
  #geom_abline(intercept = 8.388, slope = -0.829) + 
  geom_point(data=Clinton_Map, aes(x=GDP_perCapita, y=Deaths.1M.pop), color = "blue", size=2) +
  geom_point(data=Trump_Map, aes(x=GDP_perCapita, y=Deaths.1M.pop), color = "red", size=2) +
  geom_abline(intercept = -16.068, slope = 1.874, color = "blue") +
  geom_abline(intercept = 13.003, slope = -0.829, color = "red") +
  ggtitle("COVID-19 Death, Political Standing Map, and GDP") 

ggplot()+
  geom_point(data=Clinton_Map, aes(x=GDP_perCapita, y=Cases.1M.pop), color = "blue", size=2) +
  geom_point(data=Trump_Map, aes(x=GDP_perCapita, y=Cases.1M.pop), color = "red", size=2) +
  stat_function(fun = function(GDP_perCapita) -10.1383 + 1.6179*GDP_perCapita, data=Clinton_Map, color = "blue") +
  stat_function(fun = function(GDP_perCapita) 1.886 + 0.502*GDP_perCapita, data=Trump_Map, color = "red") +
  ggtitle("COVID-19 Case, Political Standing Map, and GDP")

# combine two Political Standing colums and define
full_ForMap123 <- full %>%
  select(state,Deaths.1M.pop,Clinton,Trump,GDP_perCapita) %>%
  mutate(Poli_standing = case_when(
    Clinton > Trump ~ "Clinton",
    Clinton < Trump ~ "Trump"))

# four states are very close
# Trump got Michigan, Pennsylvania, Wisconsin; Clinton got New Hampshire
full_ForMap123$Poli_standing <- replace_na(full_ForMap123$Poli_standing,"Trump")
full_ForMap123$Poli_standing[30] <- "Clinton"

# log transformation
full_ForMap123$Deaths.1M.pop <- log(full_ForMap123$Deaths.1M.pop)
full_ForMap123$GDP_perCapita <- log(full_ForMap123$GDP_perCapita)

full_ForMap1234 <- data.frame(rep(full_ForMap123$state, times=2))
full_ForMap1234$Deaths.1M.pop[1:51] <-full_ForMap123$Deaths.1M.pop
full_ForMap1234$Deaths.1M.pop[52:102] <-full_ForMap123$Deaths.1M.pop
full_ForMap1234$GDP_perCapita[1:51] <-full_ForMap123$GDP_perCapita
full_ForMap1234$GDP_perCapita[52:102] <-full_ForMap123$GDP_perCapita
full_ForMap1234$Poli_type[1:51] <-full_ForMap123$Poli_standing
full_ForMap1234$Poli_type[52:102] <-full_ForMap123$Poli_standing
full_ForMap1234$Poli_vote[1:51] <-full_ForMap123$Clinton
full_ForMap1234$Poli_vote[52:102] <-full_ForMap123$Trump
